A 48-month-old cow that died has been confirmed as having had mad cow disease the country's Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries Ministry said Thursday.
The cow was born in Shikaoi, Japan's Hokkaido region and was checked for mad cow disease after it died.
It is the second case since March in which the disease, known as bovine spongiform encephalopathy, or BSE, has been confirmed in a cow that died than having been slaughtered.
